headline: Oldest Asteroid Impact on Earth Is Found in West Australia, Researchers Say
abstract: The cataclysm, which occurred roughly 2.2 billion years ago, might have catapulted the planet out of an ice age.
lead_paragraph: Earth is constantly being pummeled by space rocks. Several tons rain down on the planet each day in the form of dust. And larger strikes have created more visible features, including giant craters. But which of our planetâ€™s extraterrestrial scars is the oldest?
